rComments: Fantastic prof! Would take his class again and definitely recommend.

I was skeptical taking this class since it was his first time teaching, but it was really clear he cared about his students and wanted us to do well. The midterm and final are content heavy but its clear what you need to know. A few quizzes that were open book and then 20% group project that was free marks. Used respondus/zoom proctoring

He doesn't have a schedule for when there would be quizzes and has no idea what will be on them until the day of. He takes months to reply to questions over email. He rushes through all the lectures and just read off the slides. Don't go to class and study off slides and external research you will be fine, he just makes things more confusing.

Anwer is a great professor who is very fair in his grading schemes on midterms. He gives lots of hints in class to what is important for tests and is willing to go over material if you don't understand it. He did do a group project in the course, but it was basically free marks if you presented something.
